Financial Ledger Orchestrator (FLO)
Documentation Master Plan (Aligned to NS-GGP Canonical Template)
PurposeThis document defines the authoritative documentation master plan for FLO, strictly aligned to the existing NS-GGP document structure (000–014).
FLO is the financial system of record and reconciliation engine for Northfield Solidarity. It does not execute trades(DAT), does not generate insights (PIE), and does not govern policy (GGP). FLO records, reconciles, attributes, and explains financial reality.
This master plan ensures:
Financial truth is centralized
Execution outcomes are reconciled
Governance and auditability extend into money flows

FLO Documentation Index (Canonical)

NS-FLO-000 — CHARTER
Purpose: Define why FLO exists
Scope:
Mission of FLO
Why financial truth must be centralized
FLO’s role within the NS engine ecosystem
Explicit non-goals (execution, governance, forecasting)
Mirrors: NS-GGP-000

NS-FLO-001 — OVERVIEW
Purpose: High-level conceptual framing
Scope:
What FLO records (transactions, balances, attribution)
Relationship to DAT (execution outcomes)
Relationship to GGP (audit & controls)
Mirrors: NS-GGP-001

